installation:
1 run:
  sudo apt-get/dnf install git

Exercise:

1 clone and set up a repo:
NOTE: this github specific
  * create an account on github.com and tell me you id.
  * git clone https://github.com/gsaucedo/udgcc.git
  * cd udgcc
  * git config user.email <whatever@something>
  * git config user.name <nickname>
  * git config core.editor <yours>

2 start editing:
  * edit asientos file and write your name at your 'asiento','fila'
    (there should be no collisions this time)
  * git status
  * git add asientos
  * git status
  * git commit
    write a meaningful message

3 check your changes
  * git log -2
  * git log

4 push your changes
NOTE: by now I should have granted you permissions
  * git pull
  * git push
  * git log -3
  * git pull
  * git log -3
  * etc.

5 create conflicts
  * repeat steps on 2 but now edit lista, add your name
  * repeat 4 (and see the conflicts)

https://github.com/gsaucedo/udgcc

sources:
http://blog.udacity.com/2015/06/a-beginners-git-github-tutorial.html
